1
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:09,000
(Watch on www.kisskh.li Support Admin)

2
00:00:09,435 --> 00:00:12,066
They say the more you
mess around with spirits,

3
00:00:12,288 --> 00:00:14,582
the easier it is for them to get to you.

4
00:00:15,685 --> 00:00:19,242
Is there any guarantee
you'll be safe every time?

5
00:00:19,731 --> 00:00:23,260
What if that ghost at the cemetery just
now tried to hurt you? What would happen?

6
00:00:23,521 --> 00:00:24,988
I could even die.

7
00:00:26,536 --> 00:00:30,414
And if one day you realize you can't back
out anymore, then you'd better move forward.

8
00:00:30,669 --> 00:00:32,112
Before it's too late.

9
00:00:32,614 --> 00:00:35,328
Thank you for the ride, P'Arthit.

10
00:00:41,011 --> 00:00:43,540
Thank you for the ride.

11
00:00:45,140 --> 00:00:46,140
P'Arthit.

12
00:01:03,561 --> 00:01:05,160
Hey, Daotok.

13
00:01:06,678 --> 00:01:08,118
You're taking this class too, North?

14
00:01:08,456 --> 00:01:11,271
Yeah. I still haven't
completed my elective credits.

15
00:01:11,737 --> 00:01:14,602
I thought I'd be lonely at
first. Good thing I ran into you.

16
00:01:16,400 --> 00:01:17,400
Yeah.

17
00:01:17,583 --> 00:01:18,869
So how's P'Arthit doing?

18
00:01:22,321 --> 00:01:26,271
After I hung up on you, I just let
him sleep on the floor like before.

19
00:01:26,462 --> 00:01:27,462
Hey!

20
00:01:27,804 --> 00:01:30,109
He didn't do anything weird, right?

21
00:01:30,573 --> 00:01:31,635
Like what?

22
00:01:32,872 --> 00:01:33,983
Oh, well...

23
00:01:34,608 --> 00:01:36,688
As long as he didn't do
anything weird, that's good.

24
00:01:37,291 --> 00:01:38,789
Did you bring your motorcycle?

25
00:01:39,857 --> 00:01:41,345
Yeah, why?

26
00:01:42,801 --> 00:01:43,878
Can I get a ride back?

27
00:01:44,751 --> 00:01:45,751
Huh?

28
00:01:45,973 --> 00:01:47,863
You didn't bring Patcharamon today?

29
00:01:50,429 --> 00:01:51,469
Then how did you get here?

30
00:01:52,530 --> 00:01:54,108
The guy next door gave me a ride.

31
00:01:54,651 --> 00:01:56,780
Why did he give you a ride?

32
00:01:57,654 --> 00:02:01,625
He saw that I wasn't feeling well,
so he was worried I couldn't drive.

33
00:02:02,429 --> 00:02:05,924
Ohhh.

34
00:02:07,330 --> 00:02:08,330
I see.

35
00:02:10,093 --> 00:02:11,967
So, are you giving me a ride or not?

36
00:02:12,288 --> 00:02:13,568
Sure. I'll take you home myself.

37
00:02:30,054 --> 00:02:33,480
You don't have to pick me up.
I'll head back with North.

38
00:02:35,928 --> 00:02:37,696
Damn it, North.

39
00:02:45,062 --> 00:02:46,663
Do you want a flat tire or what?

40
00:02:52,568 --> 00:02:55,291
Well, look who's trying to move on.

41
00:02:55,469 --> 00:02:59,085
Are you just dropping him
off and waiting to pick him up?

42
00:03:03,585 --> 00:03:05,081
So what's your deal with me?

43
00:03:06,745 --> 00:03:08,037
How so?

44
00:03:09,225 --> 00:03:10,225
You're so damn nosy.

45
00:03:20,884 --> 00:03:22,751
Do you like my friend?

46
00:03:28,685 --> 00:03:30,500
Yeah, I do.

47
00:03:30,660 --> 00:03:31,863
Satisfied?

48
00:03:35,995 --> 00:03:38,060
So what, P'? Are you going to court him?

49
00:05:41,287 --> 00:05:43,125
Hey, Daotok.

50
00:05:43,290 --> 00:05:46,028
I've got something to tell you.

51
00:05:46,373 --> 00:05:48,634
My rear tire's a bit low on air.

52
00:05:48,946 --> 00:05:52,749
So if you're going to ride on
the back, it might be dangerous.

53
00:05:53,146 --> 00:05:54,146
Then it's fine.

54
00:05:55,244 --> 00:05:57,665
I think you should have
P'Arthit pick you up.

55
00:05:58,114 --> 00:06:00,909
Hmm... I kind of want to take
a chill walk around campus.

56
00:06:01,558 --> 00:06:04,171
Oh come on, don't get
all artsy. It's dangerous.

57
00:06:04,306 --> 00:06:07,514
Walking alone is pretty deserted.

58
00:06:09,533 --> 00:06:12,948
Heeey!

59
00:06:13,157 --> 00:06:16,094
How did you get here, P'Arthit? Wow.

60
00:06:16,180 --> 00:06:18,330
I had no idea. What a coincidence.

61
00:06:18,557 --> 00:06:21,499
Wow, such a coincidence.
Man, what a coincidence.

62
00:06:21,669 --> 00:06:23,469
- How did you get here?
- Damn it, North.

63
00:06:23,714 --> 00:06:25,834
- At least make it subtle, asshole.
- Wasn't I subtle?

64
00:06:30,931 --> 00:06:31,931
How did you get here?

65
00:06:33,481 --> 00:06:35,130
I told you I'd come pick you up.

66
00:06:40,010 --> 00:06:41,010
Here.

67
00:06:42,053 --> 00:06:43,053
Hurry up.

68
00:07:16,988 --> 00:07:18,010
Thanks.

69
00:08:00,087 --> 00:08:01,167
You're unbelievable.

70
00:08:04,671 --> 00:08:05,671
What?

71
00:08:18,862 --> 00:08:20,426
I knew this would happen.

72
00:08:20,962 --> 00:08:22,122
You won't be able to move on.

73
00:08:23,702 --> 00:08:24,992
It's not that easy, P'.

74
00:08:25,558 --> 00:08:27,211
If you're going to court Daotok.

75
00:08:30,982 --> 00:08:32,445
What's so hard about that?

76
00:08:33,088 --> 00:08:34,300
So what are you going to do?

77
00:08:35,480 --> 00:08:36,755
I'll be myself.

78
00:08:37,293 --> 00:08:38,847
Be sincere. Be natural.

79
00:08:40,029 --> 00:08:42,371
I don't think you should be yourself.

80
00:08:42,948 --> 00:08:46,361
- Just try being a better person.
- Hey, North!

81
00:08:46,814 --> 00:08:47,868
Hey, hey.

82
00:08:51,725 --> 00:08:53,602
But don't rush things.

83
00:08:53,783 --> 00:08:54,927
He's closed off right now.

84
00:08:55,610 --> 00:08:56,610
Damn.

85
00:08:57,008 --> 00:08:58,008
Too late.

86
00:08:58,905 --> 00:09:00,322
I already slept hugging him.

87
00:09:01,065 --> 00:09:02,065
That's good, isn't it?

88
00:09:02,167 --> 00:09:03,976
How is that good, P'Jo?

89
00:09:04,121 --> 00:09:06,838
Well, I've done it before.

90
00:09:07,080 --> 00:09:08,580
Oh, that's enough, both of you.

91
00:09:09,254 --> 00:09:10,840
Daotok isn't me.

92
00:09:11,019 --> 00:09:12,478
If it were you, I wouldn't want you either.

93
00:09:12,502 --> 00:09:13,602
Why don't you try me?

94
00:09:13,743 --> 00:09:14,758
Asshole.

95
00:09:14,911 --> 00:09:17,471
North, what breed of dog are
you raising? It's freaking vicious.

96
00:09:17,605 --> 00:09:18,605
Damn it.

97
00:09:19,091 --> 00:09:20,091
You jerk.

98
00:09:20,743 --> 00:09:21,885
Seriously, P'.

99
00:09:22,423 --> 00:09:24,515
Daotok doesn't really
need anything anymore.

100
00:09:24,869 --> 00:09:28,186
He has a stable job.
He's happy being on his own.

101
00:09:28,930 --> 00:09:29,930
Exactly.

102
00:09:31,428 --> 00:09:33,764
And I'm freaking useless too.

103
00:09:38,173 --> 00:09:39,173
But...

104
00:09:39,980 --> 00:09:42,171
At the very least, having
me around is better.

105
00:09:42,440 --> 00:09:43,478
It makes him feel secure.

106
00:09:43,785 --> 00:09:45,700
That's it?

107
00:09:45,989 --> 00:09:48,376
Shit, what else is there, Jo?

108
00:09:50,311 --> 00:09:52,989
I... I can protect him.

109
00:09:53,637 --> 00:09:56,026
I can take care of him.
I can look after him.

110
00:09:56,270 --> 00:09:58,743
- I can be someone he can rely on.
- Someone he can rely on?

111
00:09:58,770 --> 00:09:59,388
Yeah.

112
00:09:59,417 --> 00:10:02,139
You? Someone he can rely on?
You can't even handle your own life.

113
00:10:05,228 --> 00:10:08,605
Then let me be his burden instead.
Maybe his life's just too perfect.

114
00:10:09,616 --> 00:10:11,000
Well, that could work.

115
00:10:11,063 --> 00:10:12,063
Yeah.

116
00:10:14,533 --> 00:10:15,533
I've got it.

117
00:10:17,080 --> 00:10:18,080
I think I'm handsome.

118
00:10:19,416 --> 00:10:20,416
Right?

119
00:10:21,149 --> 00:10:22,269
Isn't being handsome enough?

120
00:10:23,201 --> 00:10:24,201
You're not wrong.

121
00:10:25,388 --> 00:10:27,931
About taking care of
him—you probably could.

122
00:10:28,315 --> 00:10:31,032
And protecting him?
Yeah, you definitely can.

123
00:10:31,437 --> 00:10:32,437
But...

124
00:10:32,985 --> 00:10:34,204
Won't you cheat on him?

125
00:10:35,097 --> 00:10:36,097
No way.

126
00:10:36,693 --> 00:10:38,118
And how can you be so sure?

127
00:10:41,794 --> 00:10:43,688
If it would hurt him,

128
00:10:45,706 --> 00:10:46,706
then I won't do it.

129
00:10:48,961 --> 00:10:50,515
Damn.

130
00:11:09,909 --> 00:11:12,014
You're actually pretty nice to look at.

131
00:11:35,973 --> 00:11:37,764
Are you afraid he might like you, Michael?

132
00:11:43,238 --> 00:11:44,924
If he really does like you,

133
00:11:45,299 --> 00:11:46,432
what will you do?

134
00:11:48,816 --> 00:11:50,730
I'd probably tell him honestly

135
00:11:52,275 --> 00:11:54,265
that I'm not ready to be with anyone yet.

136
00:11:54,921 --> 00:11:56,762
Your heart's completely closed off.

137
00:11:57,748 --> 00:11:59,885
Once I'm done handling
things about his mom,

138
00:12:00,765 --> 00:12:03,250
we probably won't see
each other much anymore.

139
00:12:04,370 --> 00:12:05,948
He'll forget about me eventually.

140
00:12:07,725 --> 00:12:08,725
You think so?

141
00:12:27,757 --> 00:12:28,757
What is it?

142
00:12:30,608 --> 00:12:31,608
Well.

143
00:12:32,254 --> 00:12:33,440
I just want to be with you.

144
00:12:35,697 --> 00:12:36,697
Hey, wait.

145
00:12:41,577 --> 00:12:43,140
If you don't let me in,

146
00:12:44,148 --> 00:12:45,702
I'll really break the door down.

147
00:13:30,370 --> 00:13:31,370
North.

148
00:13:31,927 --> 00:13:34,149
The guy next door came into my room.

149
00:13:34,822 --> 00:13:35,315
Well...

150
00:13:35,700 --> 00:13:37,264
Why the hell did he came into your room?

151
00:13:37,288 --> 00:13:39,845
He said he wanted to
stay with me or something.

152
00:13:40,760 --> 00:13:41,760
Seriously?

153
00:13:42,161 --> 00:13:43,832
Wow.

154
00:13:44,130 --> 00:13:47,118
Damn, isn't that a bit much, bro?

155
00:13:47,739 --> 00:13:49,951
What should I do to make him leave my room?

156
00:13:50,671 --> 00:13:51,671
Wait...

157
00:13:51,773 --> 00:13:52,957
Don't you want him there?

158
00:13:53,637 --> 00:13:55,072
Why would I want that?

159
00:13:56,530 --> 00:13:57,885
Come on, it's obvious.

160
00:13:58,462 --> 00:13:59,551
Can't you tell

161
00:13:59,758 --> 00:14:01,440
why he's doing all this?

162
00:14:02,619 --> 00:14:04,777
Honestly, I kind of can.

163
00:14:05,623 --> 00:14:06,103
Oh?

164
00:14:06,328 --> 00:14:07,328
Really?

165
00:14:07,438 --> 00:14:09,524
Then I can openly root for him now.

166
00:14:10,385 --> 00:14:11,385
North.

167
00:14:11,928 --> 00:14:14,087
I didn't call so you could root for him.

168
00:14:14,420 --> 00:14:15,420
Come on.

169
00:14:15,995 --> 00:14:18,005
I've interrogated him. He passes.

170
00:14:20,921 --> 00:14:22,171
That's it for now, North.

171
00:14:25,125 --> 00:14:26,245
What are you doing out here?

172
00:14:28,590 --> 00:14:30,070
When are you going back to your room?

173
00:14:31,783 --> 00:14:32,783
I don't know.

174
00:14:33,331 --> 00:14:34,718
Whenever I feel like it, I guess.

175
00:14:38,656 --> 00:14:40,334
You're unbelievable.

176
00:14:42,720 --> 00:14:43,720
Let go.

177
00:14:47,374 --> 00:14:48,780
Or I'll step on your foot.

178
00:14:48,937 --> 00:14:50,971
Wow, you even gave me a warning.

179
00:14:52,137 --> 00:14:53,137
Then step on it.

180
00:14:53,453 --> 00:14:56,014
You're so tiny. How much could it hurt?

181
00:14:58,057 --> 00:15:00,816
See? You can stay still.

182
00:15:01,642 --> 00:15:03,091
That's much better. See?

183
00:15:04,290 --> 00:15:05,394
Satisfied?

184
00:15:06,777 --> 00:15:07,777
Not yet.

185
00:15:15,991 --> 00:15:17,122
Fine. I'll let go.

186
00:15:24,468 --> 00:15:25,468
Are you mad?

187
00:15:25,968 --> 00:15:26,968
Yeah.

188
00:15:27,515 --> 00:15:28,887
And you need to let go of my hand.

189
00:15:29,177 --> 00:15:30,472
I have to go to work.

190
00:15:30,997 --> 00:15:31,685
Hey.

191
00:15:31,997 --> 00:15:35,151
Aren't you even going to ask why I
held your hand? Why I hugged you?

192
00:15:35,980 --> 00:15:37,382
I don't really want to know.

193
00:15:39,825 --> 00:15:41,053
You sound so damn fierce.

194
00:15:42,303 --> 00:15:43,644
Do you dislike it that much?

195
00:15:44,133 --> 00:15:45,133
I do.

196
00:15:46,720 --> 00:15:48,346
That answer suits you perfectly.

197
00:15:49,885 --> 00:15:50,887
Can you let go now?

198
00:15:54,515 --> 00:15:55,718
What if I say no?

199
00:15:56,482 --> 00:15:57,482
Fine.

200
00:15:59,317 --> 00:16:00,428
Hey, wait.

201
00:16:23,149 --> 00:16:25,629
Are you really going to ignore
the hand I'm holding like this?

202
00:16:26,822 --> 00:16:27,822
Yes.

203
00:16:28,807 --> 00:16:30,047
If you don't stop me like this,

204
00:16:30,712 --> 00:16:32,465
it's going to get bad.

205
00:16:33,234 --> 00:16:36,208
If I get carried away and
do something more than this,

206
00:16:37,522 --> 00:16:38,844
you'll be the one in trouble.

207
00:16:39,496 --> 00:16:40,521
Don't.

208
00:16:41,625 --> 00:16:42,682
I don't like it.

209
00:16:43,182 --> 00:16:44,622
You don't like me holding your hand?

210
00:16:44,754 --> 00:16:45,992
I don't like you.

211
00:16:47,715 --> 00:16:48,771
That paid off.

212
00:16:57,651 --> 00:16:58,651
That's enough.

213
00:16:59,317 --> 00:17:00,712
This is pointless.

214
00:17:07,038 --> 00:17:08,731
You mean what I'm doing right now?

215
00:17:12,576 --> 00:17:13,958
How is it pointless?

216
00:17:14,894 --> 00:17:17,090
It's fucking great being with you.

217
00:17:25,638 --> 00:17:26,764
I like you.

218
00:17:28,994 --> 00:17:30,336
I really like you.

219
00:17:31,373 --> 00:17:33,453
I don't even know how
or why, but I like you.

220
00:17:36,875 --> 00:17:38,001
I'm sorry.

221
00:17:39,614 --> 00:17:41,828
But I don't feel that way about you.

222
00:17:43,118 --> 00:17:44,819
So please give up.

223
00:17:48,296 --> 00:17:50,481
I figured you'd say something like that.

224
00:17:51,611 --> 00:17:52,725
But sorry,

225
00:17:53,847 --> 00:17:55,819
that doesn't work on someone like me.

226
00:17:57,400 --> 00:17:58,979
You're making this hard for me.

227
00:18:02,739 --> 00:18:04,480
Then deal with it.

228
00:18:04,971 --> 00:18:07,091
Guess you didn't earn
enough merit in your past life.

229
00:18:07,210 --> 00:18:09,146
That's why someone like me likes you.

230
00:18:10,398 --> 00:18:11,917
Just accept it.

231
00:18:12,825 --> 00:18:14,823
Because I'm not backing off that easily.

232
00:18:16,311 --> 00:18:18,020
Then I'll go make more merit.

233
00:18:18,534 --> 00:18:19,534
I'll take you with me.

234
00:18:30,487 --> 00:18:31,487
Let me tell you.

235
00:18:32,410 --> 00:18:33,602
I've never had

236
00:18:33,964 --> 00:18:35,745
any of that damn love stuff.

237
00:18:36,777 --> 00:18:38,149
If I hadn't met you,

238
00:18:39,482 --> 00:18:41,614
I'd probably stay alone until I die.

239
00:18:42,862 --> 00:18:43,862
As for you,

240
00:18:45,117 --> 00:18:46,917
how you feel about me is up to you.

241
00:18:48,219 --> 00:18:50,162
What I want right now

242
00:18:51,931 --> 00:18:53,047
is to be with you.

243
00:18:58,118 --> 00:18:59,690
Just let me stay by your side.

244
00:19:03,106 --> 00:19:05,330
Then you'll be the one who gets hurt.

245
00:19:06,340 --> 00:19:07,564
Are you saying

246
00:19:09,536 --> 00:19:11,402
you'll never like me?

247
00:19:12,400 --> 00:19:14,171
What if I say yes?

248
00:19:15,764 --> 00:19:16,877
That's your business.

249
00:19:19,909 --> 00:19:20,909
I'm heading back first.

250
00:19:22,065 --> 00:19:23,065
Oh,

251
00:19:26,185 --> 00:19:27,552
don't pressure yourself.

252
00:19:28,804 --> 00:19:30,183
You can take your time liking me.

253
00:19:31,060 --> 00:19:32,060
No rush.

254
00:19:40,259 --> 00:19:41,632
Here, yum yum.

255
00:19:42,475 --> 00:19:43,798
Grow up fast, okay?

256
00:19:44,945 --> 00:19:46,742
So when are you taking your kid back?

257
00:19:47,139 --> 00:19:48,779
Are you just leaving him for me to raise?

258
00:19:50,773 --> 00:19:53,863
You're old enough to stay home
and raise your grandkid now, Direk.

259
00:19:55,146 --> 00:19:58,505
If I raise the grandkid, who's going
to earn money for you to spend?

260
00:20:00,379 --> 00:20:01,379
True.

261
00:20:01,463 --> 00:20:04,185
Then focus on your work, Direk. Got it?

262
00:20:07,945 --> 00:20:09,280
Go to sleep, kiddo.

263
00:20:14,988 --> 00:20:16,548
I'll leave him with you for now, Direk.

264
00:20:17,117 --> 00:20:18,957
I've been too busy to
take care of him lately.

265
00:20:20,448 --> 00:20:22,318
Oh, I just bought you a new car.

266
00:20:23,004 --> 00:20:24,004
Seriously?

267
00:20:24,564 --> 00:20:25,564
For racing.

268
00:20:28,927 --> 00:20:31,770
You never do anything without expecting
something in return, do you, Direk?

269
00:20:31,794 --> 00:20:33,287
This match is important.

270
00:20:33,762 --> 00:20:35,911
You're racing against that family's son.

271
00:20:36,020 --> 00:20:38,657
If you lose, you'll look like a
damn fool. I'm telling you now.

272
00:20:38,792 --> 00:20:40,065
So go practice.

273
00:20:41,232 --> 00:20:42,721
Don't you trust me, Direk?

274
00:20:43,928 --> 00:20:45,271
I do.

275
00:20:45,783 --> 00:20:47,946
But you've been away
from the track for a while.

276
00:20:48,228 --> 00:20:49,228
Don't be careless.

277
00:20:50,223 --> 00:20:52,622
I'm not sure if I'll have
time to practice, Direk.

278
00:20:53,442 --> 00:20:56,245
Fourth year is insane. I
barely have time to sleep.

279
00:20:57,429 --> 00:20:58,506
Classes,

280
00:20:58,840 --> 00:21:00,223
clinical rounds, exams

281
00:21:00,958 --> 00:21:02,765
it's driving me crazy.

282
00:21:03,896 --> 00:21:05,038
Then just drop out.

283
00:21:06,010 --> 00:21:07,010
What?

284
00:21:07,195 --> 00:21:09,668
Didn't you say you wanted
that degree to hang on your wall?

285
00:21:10,177 --> 00:21:11,177
I was just saying that.

286
00:21:11,663 --> 00:21:13,488
I just see how tired and stressed you are.

287
00:21:14,623 --> 00:21:15,857
But if you graduate,

288
00:21:16,628 --> 00:21:17,924
your mom would be proud.

289
00:21:19,082 --> 00:21:21,979
Hmm. So proud.

290
00:21:22,423 --> 00:21:23,423
"Dylan,

291
00:21:23,706 --> 00:21:25,601
did you got F again?"

292
00:21:28,598 --> 00:21:29,598
Hey, Direk.

293
00:21:31,930 --> 00:21:33,282
I have something to tell you.

294
00:21:34,441 --> 00:21:35,697
Did you get some girl pregnant?

295
00:21:36,565 --> 00:21:38,700
No? That's bad then, Direk.

296
00:21:38,810 --> 00:21:40,226
Or did you kill someone?

297
00:21:40,616 --> 00:21:43,760
- No.
- Don't tell me you stole something.

298
00:21:43,859 --> 00:21:45,293
This is getting out of hand, Direk.

299
00:21:45,352 --> 00:21:47,672
- Did you do something illegal?
- Are you going to help me?

300
00:21:47,810 --> 00:21:49,300
Yeah, to kick you while you're down.

301
00:21:49,488 --> 00:21:51,256
I've taught you that since you were a kid.

302
00:21:51,420 --> 00:21:54,922
That you must never do anything
illegal or cause trouble for anyone.

303
00:21:56,017 --> 00:21:57,017
Oh, come on.

304
00:21:57,146 --> 00:21:58,146
Fine, I'll tell you.

305
00:22:02,057 --> 00:22:04,712
Just don't have a heart attack.
You're not getting any younger.

306
00:22:09,099 --> 00:22:10,383
I like someone.

307
00:22:12,352 --> 00:22:13,616
I'm courting him right now.

308
00:22:15,484 --> 00:22:16,641
Shit.

309
00:22:17,662 --> 00:22:20,320
This is worse than you killing someone.

310
00:22:23,042 --> 00:22:24,042
Who is it?

311
00:22:48,860 --> 00:22:49,900
What are you listening to?

312
00:22:50,961 --> 00:22:51,961
The same playlist.

313
00:22:54,251 --> 00:22:55,251
Let me listen too.

314
00:22:56,257 --> 00:22:58,743
- Your shirt's dirty.
- Hey, it's washable.

315
00:23:14,770 --> 00:23:16,869
Hey, my face.

316
00:23:17,429 --> 00:23:19,816
It's not a sketchpad. It's my face. Move.

317
00:23:23,158 --> 00:23:24,158
Then get up.

318
00:23:25,656 --> 00:23:26,656
No.

319
00:23:42,456 --> 00:23:43,493
How was class?

320
00:23:47,191 --> 00:23:48,191
Same as usual.

321
00:23:49,494 --> 00:23:52,053
My case presentation this
morning was fucking awful.

322
00:23:54,031 --> 00:23:55,620
Ward rounds were exhausting as hell.

323
00:24:00,685 --> 00:24:01,685
Hey.

324
00:24:02,429 --> 00:24:03,429
Hmm?

325
00:24:04,131 --> 00:24:05,251
I want to ask you something.

326
00:24:07,037 --> 00:24:08,037
What is it?

327
00:24:10,715 --> 00:24:11,960
Why do you like me?

328
00:24:18,905 --> 00:24:20,951
That's a question I
can't really answer either.

329
00:24:22,829 --> 00:24:24,032
I just know it has to be you.

330
00:24:28,945 --> 00:24:29,945
Are you tired?

331
00:24:31,189 --> 00:24:32,189
Not really.

332
00:24:42,524 --> 00:24:44,730
Is there anything you don't like about me?

333
00:24:46,371 --> 00:24:47,371
Why?

334
00:24:47,728 --> 00:24:48,840
Are you going to fix it?

335
00:24:49,912 --> 00:24:50,928
I'll do worse than that.

336
00:24:55,725 --> 00:24:56,725
Nothing.

337
00:24:59,749 --> 00:25:00,829
That's impossible.

338
00:25:02,851 --> 00:25:03,851
Why?

339
00:25:05,139 --> 00:25:06,317
There has to be something.

340
00:25:08,120 --> 00:25:10,214
Something you don't like about in human.

341
00:25:16,131 --> 00:25:17,485
But I won't ask you

342
00:25:18,711 --> 00:25:20,426
what you don't like about me.

343
00:25:21,659 --> 00:25:22,659
Why not?

344
00:25:24,069 --> 00:25:26,048
Because you'd definitely say everything.

345
00:25:30,610 --> 00:25:31,610
No, I wouldn't.

346
00:25:37,263 --> 00:25:38,263
Really?

347
00:25:41,245 --> 00:25:42,245
Then…

348
00:25:43,840 --> 00:25:45,265
What do you like about me?

349
00:25:51,248 --> 00:25:52,425
You're natural.

350
00:25:54,877 --> 00:25:55,877
Me?

351
00:25:56,865 --> 00:25:57,865
Yeah.

352
00:25:59,428 --> 00:26:00,428
You don't lie.

353
00:26:01,640 --> 00:26:03,405
I feel comfortable when I'm with you.

354
00:26:04,819 --> 00:26:07,002
Even if sometimes I don't
feel like being around you.

355
00:26:10,484 --> 00:26:12,739
But when I am with you, I feel at ease.

356
00:26:15,651 --> 00:26:16,651
Wait.

357
00:26:17,417 --> 00:26:18,417
Hey.

358
00:26:19,047 --> 00:26:20,340
I'm not ready for this.

359
00:26:22,162 --> 00:26:23,697
Are you confessing to me?

360
00:26:25,417 --> 00:26:26,417
Not at all.

361
00:26:28,482 --> 00:26:30,285
It feels relieved, like when I'm with North.

362
00:26:31,401 --> 00:26:33,065
But more annoying.

363
00:26:34,028 --> 00:26:35,028
Way more.

364
00:26:38,294 --> 00:26:38,939
Shit.

365
00:26:39,306 --> 00:26:41,468
The way you talk,

366
00:26:42,235 --> 00:26:43,235
damn.

367
00:26:43,293 --> 00:26:44,614
If it weren't me,

368
00:26:44,922 --> 00:26:46,631
someone would be crying by now.

369
00:26:47,884 --> 00:26:50,413
Good thing I'm built for all weather.

370
00:26:51,459 --> 00:26:53,546
Even if you told me you hate me,

371
00:26:54,558 --> 00:26:55,558
I wouldn't be hurt.

372
00:26:56,863 --> 00:26:58,361
I hate you.

373
00:27:02,023 --> 00:27:03,023
Really?

374
00:27:04,712 --> 00:27:05,891
Not exactly hate.

375
00:27:08,459 --> 00:27:09,681
That still hit hard, damn.

376
00:27:11,678 --> 00:27:13,425
Come on, say it again.

377
00:27:14,078 --> 00:27:15,527
I hate you.

378
00:27:23,259 --> 00:27:24,598
Damn, I really can't handle that.

379
00:27:25,114 --> 00:27:27,971
No, no. Don't say that word again.

380
00:27:28,724 --> 00:27:30,549
Even if you really hate me,

381
00:27:30,645 --> 00:27:31,645
just

382
00:27:32,324 --> 00:27:34,284
keep it to yourself. Don't
say it out loud again.

383
00:27:35,662 --> 00:27:36,662
Mm.

384
00:27:52,659 --> 00:27:54,162
My dad invited you over for dinner.

385
00:27:56,920 --> 00:27:57,960
Don't even think about it.

386
00:27:58,174 --> 00:27:59,174
You can't refuse.

387
00:28:00,016 --> 00:28:01,768
Why did he suddenly invite me?

388
00:28:02,786 --> 00:28:03,333
Well,

389
00:28:03,717 --> 00:28:06,296
I told him I like you.

390
00:28:07,146 --> 00:28:08,146
So he invited you.

391
00:28:08,857 --> 00:28:10,417
Thanks for the ride.

392
00:28:11,460 --> 00:28:13,208
Wait, wait.

393
00:28:16,780 --> 00:28:18,697
Since I started courting you,

394
00:28:20,728 --> 00:28:22,641
- How many points have I earned?
- None at all.

395
00:28:23,588 --> 00:28:24,588
What?

396
00:28:26,026 --> 00:28:27,026
None at all?

397
00:28:30,709 --> 00:28:32,551
You've earned my gratitude.

398
00:28:37,248 --> 00:28:38,642
Then where's the thank you?

399
00:28:40,499 --> 00:28:41,499
Thank you.

400
00:28:43,400 --> 00:28:44,400
Thank who?

401
00:28:47,241 --> 00:28:48,241
Thank you,

402
00:28:48,640 --> 00:28:49,640
P'Arthit.

403
00:28:50,484 --> 00:28:51,610
Smile too.

404
00:28:54,259 --> 00:28:55,365
Do I have to smile too?

405
00:28:55,628 --> 00:28:56,628
Mm-hm.

406
00:29:02,251 --> 00:29:03,251
There.

407
00:29:04,364 --> 00:29:05,420
Say it with a smile.

408
00:29:08,302 --> 00:29:11,351
Thank you, P'Arthit.

409
00:29:14,281 --> 00:29:15,434
That's more like it.

410
00:29:16,219 --> 00:29:17,905
That's better.

411
00:29:18,687 --> 00:29:19,687
Yeah.

412
00:29:21,284 --> 00:29:22,284
Let's go.

413
00:29:37,700 --> 00:29:40,019
You're surprised I invited
you today, aren't you?

414
00:29:41,665 --> 00:29:42,665
Yes.

415
00:29:44,155 --> 00:29:48,767
From when he was little until now, Arthit
has never told me about something like this.

416
00:29:48,860 --> 00:29:49,979
This is the first time.

417
00:29:50,487 --> 00:29:52,229
So I got a little excited.

418
00:29:52,431 --> 00:29:53,431
You understand, right?

419
00:29:54,668 --> 00:29:55,668
I understand.

420
00:29:57,154 --> 00:29:58,154
So,

421
00:29:58,435 --> 00:30:00,173
he's courting you, right?

422
00:30:01,229 --> 00:30:02,229
And…

423
00:30:02,345 --> 00:30:03,517
Are you okay with that?

424
00:30:04,890 --> 00:30:06,770
It must be putting you
in a difficult position.

425
00:30:11,742 --> 00:30:13,734
Let me apologize on behalf of my son.

426
00:30:14,011 --> 00:30:15,011
He's…

427
00:30:15,822 --> 00:30:17,155
Not very well-behaved.

428
00:30:17,502 --> 00:30:19,334
He's so spoiled.

429
00:30:19,503 --> 00:30:20,543
And he has a sharp tongue.

430
00:30:22,291 --> 00:30:23,500
Hey, Direk.

431
00:30:23,808 --> 00:30:25,117
Why are you badmouthing me?

432
00:30:25,367 --> 00:30:26,367
What?

433
00:30:26,730 --> 00:30:28,277
I'm telling the truth.

434
00:30:32,151 --> 00:30:33,231
It must be exhausting, huh?

435
00:30:34,226 --> 00:30:35,226
I'm not exhausted.

436
00:30:37,229 --> 00:30:38,853
I wasn't talking to you.

437
00:30:39,445 --> 00:30:40,617
I was talking to Daotok.

438
00:30:41,928 --> 00:30:44,853
It's tiring, right? Having Arthit
follow you around like this.

439
00:30:45,324 --> 00:30:46,334
It's not tiring.

440
00:30:46,576 --> 00:30:47,946
But it's annoying.

441
00:30:53,010 --> 00:30:54,702
That must've made you want to cry.

442
00:30:56,773 --> 00:30:57,773
I'm fine.

443
00:30:58,488 --> 00:30:59,671
I've had worse.

444
00:31:00,045 --> 00:31:01,925
"You should spend your
time on something else."

445
00:31:02,121 --> 00:31:04,997
"Why do you even like me?
Why don't you like someone else?"

446
00:31:05,397 --> 00:31:07,702
"Just give up. I don't like you."

447
00:31:07,884 --> 00:31:09,160
"Stop bothering me."

448
00:31:10,598 --> 00:31:11,598
My son

449
00:31:11,811 --> 00:31:13,266
got chased away like a stray dog.

450
00:31:17,354 --> 00:31:19,299
The reason I invited you today

451
00:31:19,466 --> 00:31:21,965
is to thank you about Arthit's mother.

452
00:31:22,832 --> 00:31:26,325
Since you came back from San Francisco,
we haven't had the chance to meet.

453
00:31:28,192 --> 00:31:29,392
It's really no problem at all.

454
00:31:31,640 --> 00:31:33,687
Oh, and Arthit showed me a photo

455
00:31:34,278 --> 00:31:36,154
of the painting you continued from Emma's.

456
00:31:36,580 --> 00:31:37,940
It's very beautiful.

457
00:31:38,386 --> 00:31:40,666
Would you be interested
in doing a painting for me?

458
00:31:42,414 --> 00:31:44,087
What kind of work do you like?

459
00:31:44,958 --> 00:31:46,905
Hmm, I like acrylics.

460
00:31:47,066 --> 00:31:49,100
The bolder the colors, the better.

461
00:31:50,090 --> 00:31:51,090
Sure.

462
00:31:52,125 --> 00:31:52,822
Really?

463
00:31:53,060 --> 00:31:55,897
Then I'll have my secretary
send you the details.

464
00:31:56,914 --> 00:32:00,951
You mean acrylic paint on
canvas, something like that?

465
00:32:01,087 --> 00:32:05,065
Yes. I'll show you some
examples of what I like.

466
00:32:05,296 --> 00:32:06,392
Here, something like this.

467
00:32:22,872 --> 00:32:24,232
You're not uncomfortable, are you?

468
00:32:25,632 --> 00:32:26,632
Not at all.

469
00:32:30,145 --> 00:32:32,487
My dad's always like
this when he's with me.

470
00:32:33,940 --> 00:32:34,940
You're okay, right?

471
00:32:35,417 --> 00:32:35,951
Mm.

472
00:32:36,311 --> 00:32:37,311
Of course I am.

473
00:32:39,840 --> 00:32:41,204
Why did you bring me here?

474
00:32:45,106 --> 00:32:46,106
Well.

475
00:32:48,508 --> 00:32:50,881
I wanted you to see the real me.

476
00:32:52,570 --> 00:32:55,125
This is my dad. My family.

477
00:32:56,791 --> 00:32:58,311
There's nothing left to hide from you.

478
00:32:59,617 --> 00:33:02,044
If anyone says I'm not serious about you,

479
00:33:03,324 --> 00:33:04,924
I'll kick them in the face.

480
00:33:10,711 --> 00:33:11,711
Thank you.

481
00:33:12,601 --> 00:33:13,601
Huh?

482
00:33:14,831 --> 00:33:15,831
Thank you.

483
00:33:17,468 --> 00:33:18,579
For being serious.

484
00:33:22,863 --> 00:33:24,611
Thank you for being serious about me.

485
00:33:27,459 --> 00:33:28,459
Mm.

486
00:33:30,160 --> 00:33:31,570
Not everyone

487
00:33:31,891 --> 00:33:33,820
would trust someone like this,

488
00:33:35,241 --> 00:33:36,862
bringing them home

489
00:33:38,038 --> 00:33:39,179
the way you did.

490
00:33:39,333 --> 00:33:41,345
It's because you're
serious about me, right?

491
00:33:45,823 --> 00:33:48,401
Why do you sound like
you're opening up to me?

492
00:33:57,272 --> 00:33:58,595
Zero points.

493
00:33:59,660 --> 00:34:01,397
What? Why?

494
00:34:03,567 --> 00:34:05,634
Zero out of nothing at all.

495
00:34:11,042 --> 00:34:12,946
From now on, I'm
starting to count the points.

496
00:34:51,160 --> 00:34:52,160
P'Earng.

497
00:35:04,308 --> 00:35:06,915
If you want to play with
Johan, just say so nicely.

498
00:35:08,388 --> 00:35:10,157
I'll leave the lights on for you.

499
00:35:23,800 --> 00:35:24,905
Is the power out?

500
00:35:26,392 --> 00:35:29,268
The other rooms still have power.

501
00:35:36,823 --> 00:35:38,478
It's not just a burnt-out bulb.

502
00:35:39,463 --> 00:35:40,853
All the electricity in the room

503
00:35:41,262 --> 00:35:42,262
is completely out.

504
00:35:44,198 --> 00:35:45,198
Really?

505
00:35:46,607 --> 00:35:47,650
It's already late.

506
00:35:48,459 --> 00:35:53,426
I'll have a technician take a look tomorrow. Tonight,
Dao, you'll have to sleep somewhere else first.

507
00:35:56,088 --> 00:35:57,259
It's okay.

508
00:35:57,847 --> 00:35:59,728
I can sleep in the room tonight.

509
00:36:05,490 --> 00:36:07,040
Hey, you can't.

510
00:36:07,580 --> 00:36:09,282
There's no electricity,
and the AC isn't working.

511
00:36:09,306 --> 00:36:12,008
How are you going to sleep?
What if something happens to you?

512
00:36:12,389 --> 00:36:14,097
And there are so many ghosts in that room.

513
00:36:14,540 --> 00:36:15,540
No way.

514
00:36:16,205 --> 00:36:17,290
He's right, Dao.

515
00:36:18,385 --> 00:36:19,754
If you don't want the hassle,

516
00:36:20,278 --> 00:36:21,838
you can sleep in the next room for now.

517
00:36:21,894 --> 00:36:22,894
Mm.

518
00:36:24,802 --> 00:36:26,074
You're being unusually nice.

519
00:36:26,392 --> 00:36:27,392
Really?

520
00:36:27,423 --> 00:36:27,983
Yeah.

521
00:36:28,241 --> 00:36:29,241
I'm being nice?

522
00:36:29,466 --> 00:36:31,586
The nicest you've ever
been since I've known you, P'.

523
00:36:48,277 --> 00:36:50,505
Hey, you can let John sleep here.

524
00:36:52,517 --> 00:36:53,811
Uh… how do I set this up?

525
00:36:59,973 --> 00:37:00,973
Stay here, okay?

526
00:37:03,072 --> 00:37:04,072
Mr. John.

527
00:37:11,585 --> 00:37:12,954
Where did you even get John from?

528
00:37:14,392 --> 00:37:16,037
From my old dorm.

529
00:37:17,044 --> 00:37:18,343
They didn't allow pets there.

530
00:37:19,823 --> 00:37:21,321
Did you move because of him?

531
00:37:22,231 --> 00:37:23,231
Yeah.

532
00:37:26,515 --> 00:37:28,887
What are you, Cupid or something?

533
00:37:38,377 --> 00:37:39,817
I think John likes me more than you.

534
00:37:43,137 --> 00:37:44,189
Mr. John.

535
00:37:44,321 --> 00:37:46,962
Don't do that. Come back to me.

536
00:37:48,419 --> 00:37:49,472
Come back to me, okay?

537
00:37:52,965 --> 00:37:55,885
See? Now you've made him all dramatic
over you. What are you going to do?

538
00:37:56,026 --> 00:37:57,887
Do you like him more than me, Mr. John?

539
00:38:03,937 --> 00:38:05,174
Hey, hey.

540
00:38:05,594 --> 00:38:06,786
Go sleep properly on the bed.

541
00:38:07,294 --> 00:38:08,485
Don't sit on the sofa.

542
00:38:09,988 --> 00:38:10,988
Go.

543
00:38:13,909 --> 00:38:16,617
I'm going to sit and work. You
go sleep properly on the bed.

544
00:38:17,425 --> 00:38:17,842
Go.

545
00:38:18,414 --> 00:38:19,414
Now.

546
00:38:20,245 --> 00:38:21,245
Go sleep on the bed.

547
00:38:22,573 --> 00:38:23,573
Are you sure?

548
00:38:23,859 --> 00:38:24,859
Yeah.

549
00:38:25,373 --> 00:38:26,813
I'm not going to do anything to you.

550
00:38:27,589 --> 00:38:28,589
Go.

551
00:38:32,447 --> 00:38:33,447
Go.

552
00:39:42,974 --> 00:39:44,007
Are you hungry?

553
00:39:52,770 --> 00:39:54,739
Someone already fed you.

554
00:40:17,008 --> 00:40:19,419
You can keep my spare keycard for now.

555
00:40:19,862 --> 00:40:22,262
I went for a run this morning
and passed by a soy milk shop,

556
00:40:22,542 --> 00:40:23,557
so I bought some for you.

557
00:40:24,506 --> 00:40:25,751
I've already fed John.

558
00:40:45,108 --> 00:40:46,108
You're awake?

559
00:40:54,197 --> 00:40:55,503
You look so bright.

560
00:40:58,930 --> 00:41:01,010
Ever since you started
liking my boyfriend's friend.

561
00:41:04,277 --> 00:41:05,423
Who told you that?

562
00:41:16,349 --> 00:41:18,844
Come on, I'm ready. Hit me with it.

563
00:41:19,011 --> 00:41:20,011
Go ahead and scold me.

564
00:41:20,685 --> 00:41:21,197
What?

565
00:41:21,525 --> 00:41:22,648
You're not going to scold me?

566
00:41:22,672 --> 00:41:23,672
Why would I?

567
00:41:24,994 --> 00:41:25,994
Well…

568
00:41:26,688 --> 00:41:28,471
When Jo first started pursuing North,

569
00:41:28,918 --> 00:41:31,028
I saw you grilling him relentlessly.

570
00:41:31,604 --> 00:41:33,102
You and Jo aren't the same.

571
00:41:33,699 --> 00:41:35,019
You've never liked anyone before.

572
00:41:35,580 --> 00:41:36,634
So this time,

573
00:41:37,059 --> 00:41:38,059
you really like him.

574
00:41:40,380 --> 00:41:41,380
Hill, my dear friend.

575
00:41:42,140 --> 00:41:45,805
I knew it. You'd understand me.

576
00:41:46,318 --> 00:41:47,838
You're seriously a ride-or-die friend.

577
00:41:52,330 --> 00:41:53,800
I'm not dying with you.

578
00:41:58,951 --> 00:41:59,951
But I admit it,

579
00:42:01,442 --> 00:42:04,151
I was a little surprised that
you found someone you like.

580
00:42:05,207 --> 00:42:07,362
If I say I'm proud of you…

581
00:42:07,600 --> 00:42:09,020
Would that be too much?

582
00:42:09,554 --> 00:42:10,847
Damn it.

583
00:42:11,605 --> 00:42:13,912
Are you saying you're proud of me?

584
00:42:14,379 --> 00:42:15,379
Hill.

585
00:42:16,240 --> 00:42:18,011
Can you be my dad instead of Direk?

586
00:42:19,240 --> 00:42:21,480
You're so damn warm and kind.

587
00:42:21,783 --> 00:42:25,250
I'm seriously touched by you, Hill.

588
00:42:26,893 --> 00:42:28,274
I don't want a son like you.

589
00:42:28,776 --> 00:42:30,462
Aw, Dad.

590
00:42:31,197 --> 00:42:33,360
I haven't even called Direk “Dad” yet.

591
00:42:33,595 --> 00:42:36,370
By the way, can I get some
money to modify my car?

592
00:42:36,598 --> 00:42:37,721
Go away.

593
00:42:39,854 --> 00:42:42,789
You never chase Jo away like that.

594
00:42:43,340 --> 00:42:46,346
- But you chase me away like I'm nothing.
- I chase Jo away too.

595
00:42:47,565 --> 00:42:49,125
Talking to you is such a waste of time.

596
00:42:50,534 --> 00:42:51,534
Hey.

597
00:42:52,180 --> 00:42:55,253
Wait, Hill. Hey, give me
some money first, Hill!

598
00:43:19,568 --> 00:43:22,168
I heard P'Pae said your room
needs repairs for several more days.

599
00:43:22,320 --> 00:43:23,320
Yeah.

600
00:43:23,715 --> 00:43:25,465
He said the electrical system's broken.

601
00:43:27,426 --> 00:43:29,174
Then you have to stay in my room for now.

602
00:43:29,678 --> 00:43:30,962
Am I bothering you?

603
00:43:31,863 --> 00:43:32,949
Bothering me how?

604
00:43:34,114 --> 00:43:36,533
It was my plan all along—to
make your room lose power.

605
00:43:44,245 --> 00:43:45,245
Hey.

606
00:43:45,466 --> 00:43:47,770
I'm kidding. Damn, did
you actually believe me?

607
00:43:53,749 --> 00:43:55,269
What kind of person do you think I am?

608
00:44:17,817 --> 00:44:19,988
Try drawing what your dad asked me to draw.

609
00:44:20,900 --> 00:44:22,825
I'm thinking about whether he'll like it.

610
00:44:30,429 --> 00:44:31,653
Of course he will.

611
00:44:32,783 --> 00:44:34,293
This is totally Direk's style.

612
00:44:50,552 --> 00:44:51,552
Shit.

613
00:45:00,826 --> 00:45:02,048
Go on, keep drawing.

614
00:45:03,269 --> 00:45:04,669
You can use my head as a sketchpad.

615
00:45:07,533 --> 00:45:09,278
I'm really exhausted today.

616
00:45:11,322 --> 00:45:12,976
Then go sleep on the bed.

617
00:45:13,746 --> 00:45:15,739
Sleeping on the bed won't
make me any less tired.

618
00:45:20,925 --> 00:45:21,997
Not if you're not there.

619
00:45:52,845 --> 00:45:54,619
He looks really exhausted.

620
00:45:58,749 --> 00:46:00,496
He studied hard all day.

621
00:46:01,322 --> 00:46:02,874
And he has to wake up early.

622
00:46:04,791 --> 00:46:06,202
Even if he's rude

623
00:46:06,484 --> 00:46:08,010
or seems a bit harsh,

624
00:46:08,395 --> 00:46:11,037
his love is actually
very pure, like a child's.

625
00:46:18,250 --> 00:46:19,485
If it's this person,

626
00:46:21,819 --> 00:46:22,825
it should be safe.

627
00:46:24,488 --> 00:46:25,488
Yeah.

628
00:46:25,903 --> 00:46:26,985
It should be safe.

629
00:46:33,125 --> 00:46:34,742
If he can endure it.

630
00:46:36,299 --> 00:46:38,183
Isn't he the one you want?

631
00:46:38,887 --> 00:46:41,487
The one who'll wait until you're
brave enough to open your heart.

632
00:46:49,466 --> 00:46:50,954
Nothing's certain.

633
00:46:51,997 --> 00:46:53,588
People can change.

634
00:46:54,502 --> 00:46:56,068
You're hoping, aren't you,

635
00:46:56,971 --> 00:46:58,142
that he won't change.

636
00:48:39,601 --> 00:48:40,601
What are you doing?

637
00:48:43,678 --> 00:48:45,143
Doing what I want to do.

638
00:48:59,712 --> 00:49:00,712
You...

639
00:49:14,897 --> 00:49:15,897
Get out.

640
00:49:41,611 --> 00:49:43,620
You said you wouldn't do anything.

641
00:49:51,045 --> 00:49:52,045
I'm sorry.

642
00:49:58,780 --> 00:50:00,114
I don't understand it either.

643
00:50:01,659 --> 00:50:03,250
I don't know what came over me.

644
00:50:20,188 --> 00:50:21,188
Does it hurt?

645
00:50:22,388 --> 00:50:23,388
No.

646
00:50:24,466 --> 00:50:26,093
It doesn't hurt at all.

647
00:50:42,668 --> 00:50:44,404
I really like you.

648
00:50:46,813 --> 00:50:47,928
I like you so much.

649
00:50:52,720 --> 00:50:54,527
I didn't think it'd be this much.

650
00:51:00,222 --> 00:51:01,222
It is that much.

651
00:51:19,457 --> 00:51:20,617
Go sleep properly on the bed.

652
00:51:22,465 --> 00:51:23,515
No.

653
00:51:25,231 --> 00:51:26,231
You...

654
00:51:28,317 --> 00:51:29,317
No.

655
00:51:30,487 --> 00:51:31,607
Do you want me to carry you?

656
00:51:31,863 --> 00:51:33,192
Do you want me to deduct points?

657
00:51:33,352 --> 00:51:34,462
Do you think I'm scared?

658
00:51:34,662 --> 00:51:35,927
And you're not scared?

659
00:51:59,431 --> 00:52:01,322
Can you stop scaring me like that?

660
00:52:04,893 --> 00:52:06,118
I'll try.

661
00:52:15,142 --> 00:52:16,142
And…

662
00:52:19,140 --> 00:52:20,715
How many points are left now?

663
00:52:24,690 --> 00:52:25,739
Minus one.

664
00:52:27,345 --> 00:52:28,671
For scaring me.

665
00:52:30,965 --> 00:52:31,995
Hey.

666
00:52:32,416 --> 00:52:33,647
Come on.

667
00:52:34,063 --> 00:52:35,860
I've already reflected on it.

668
00:52:36,804 --> 00:52:37,927
Let's cancel it out to zero.

669
00:52:39,362 --> 00:52:40,362
Please?

670
00:52:40,931 --> 00:52:42,595
- Oh.
- Mm.

671
00:52:43,404 --> 00:52:44,410
You want zero?

672
00:52:45,042 --> 00:52:46,042
Mm.

673
00:52:47,937 --> 00:52:50,121
Since you feel guilty,
I'll give you two points.

674
00:52:50,853 --> 00:52:53,520
Minus one leaves you with one.

675
00:52:54,888 --> 00:52:57,511
But if you want zero, that's fine.

676
00:52:58,690 --> 00:53:01,288
One. One. I'll take one.

677
00:53:01,312 --> 00:53:02,533
Pleaaase.

678
00:53:03,170 --> 00:53:04,170
One.

679
00:53:05,210 --> 00:53:06,330
Please.

680
00:53:07,127 --> 00:53:08,127
One.

681
00:53:10,979 --> 00:53:12,318
Okay? One.

682
00:53:13,340 --> 00:53:14,340
I'll take one.

683
00:55:20,454 --> 00:55:23,054
After you graduate, are you going
to work as a doctor right away?

684
00:55:26,724 --> 00:55:27,736
Definitely not.

685
00:55:28,884 --> 00:55:29,884
Why?

686
00:55:31,828 --> 00:55:34,048
I promised my mom I'd study medicine.

687
00:55:35,068 --> 00:55:36,709
So once I graduate, that's it.

688
00:55:37,748 --> 00:55:39,097
If I had to keep being a doctor,

689
00:55:39,792 --> 00:55:41,512
I'd probably end up fighting with patients.

690
00:55:43,866 --> 00:55:48,118
Even now, when I'm on ward duty, I have
to use up a lifetime's worth of patience.

691
00:55:48,534 --> 00:55:50,234
You're doing really well.

692
00:55:51,872 --> 00:55:52,872
Really?

693
00:55:53,057 --> 00:55:54,057
Mm.

694
00:55:54,697 --> 00:55:55,697
You're amazing.

695
00:55:57,428 --> 00:55:58,788
You're praising me like I'm a dog.

696
00:55:59,602 --> 00:56:00,842
Why don't you pat my head then?

697
00:56:08,278 --> 00:56:11,457
You've really done well all this time.

698
00:56:18,343 --> 00:56:19,776
My tail's wagging already.

699
00:56:24,600 --> 00:56:25,600
Let's go.

700
00:56:43,125 --> 00:56:45,214
Are John and I the same status to you?

701
00:56:53,231 --> 00:56:54,231
I love you.

702
00:56:54,611 --> 00:56:55,611
Hmm?

703
00:56:57,791 --> 00:56:59,013
I said I love you.

704
00:56:59,700 --> 00:57:01,300
Why are you saying that all of a sudden?

705
00:57:01,728 --> 00:57:02,776
I just wanted to.

706
00:57:03,862 --> 00:57:05,422
I thought it was just “like,” not love.

707
00:57:06,623 --> 00:57:07,623
No.

708
00:57:09,170 --> 00:57:10,511
I think it's love now.

709
00:57:26,810 --> 00:57:27,810
What are you smiling at?

710
00:57:29,588 --> 00:57:30,906
Dad sent me a picture.

711
00:57:31,776 --> 00:57:33,355
The one who used to come to your room.

712
00:57:33,725 --> 00:57:34,725
Yeah.

713
00:57:35,161 --> 00:57:36,161
That one.

714
00:57:36,281 --> 00:57:37,281
Go break up with him.

715
00:57:38,124 --> 00:57:39,305
Cut him off completely.

716
00:57:40,085 --> 00:57:41,466
I can't cut him off.

717
00:57:41,671 --> 00:57:42,671
Why not?

718
00:57:45,211 --> 00:57:47,404
Dad is my other father.

719
00:57:51,725 --> 00:57:53,813
My mom and dad separated.

720
00:57:54,311 --> 00:57:56,407
Papa started a new relationship with Dad.

721
00:57:56,970 --> 00:57:59,026
They've both raised me since I was little.

722
00:58:01,192 --> 00:58:02,508
Why didn't you tell me?

723
00:58:03,266 --> 00:58:05,226
How was I supposed to
know you'd think like that?

724
00:58:08,746 --> 00:58:09,746
So that means…

725
00:58:10,459 --> 00:58:11,914
You don't have anyone, right?

726
00:58:12,909 --> 00:58:13,909
No.

727
00:58:14,477 --> 00:58:17,266
If I did, I wouldn't let you get this close.

728
00:58:20,256 --> 00:58:21,256
Damn.

729
00:58:21,706 --> 00:58:23,060
That makes me feel special.

730
00:58:25,980 --> 00:58:26,980
Hey.

731
00:58:27,281 --> 00:58:29,099
Why don't you just be my boyfriend already?

732
00:58:29,177 --> 00:58:30,177
No.

733
00:58:30,739 --> 00:58:32,936
What? Not even for a second?

734
00:58:33,831 --> 00:58:34,831
Just a little?

735
00:58:36,500 --> 00:58:37,500
Just a little.

736
00:58:44,817 --> 00:58:47,752
So what's going on with you and P'Arthit?

737
00:58:48,045 --> 00:58:50,687
When I first heard about
it, I couldn't believe my ears.

738
00:58:51,285 --> 00:58:55,324
- When North told me, I believed it even less.
- Damn you.

739
00:58:56,962 --> 00:58:58,290
Were you really that shocked?

740
00:58:58,551 --> 00:58:59,551
Of course I was.

741
00:58:59,760 --> 00:59:01,671
That's P'Arthit we're talking about.

742
00:59:01,939 --> 00:59:03,362
- This is Dao.
- Yeah.

743
00:59:03,910 --> 00:59:08,825
They're both in the sky, but one's
day and the other's night. Like that.

744
00:59:09,878 --> 00:59:11,642
Hey, but I think they match.

745
00:59:11,779 --> 00:59:12,902
P'Thit is hot-tempered,

746
00:59:13,155 --> 00:59:14,155
and you're cool.

747
00:59:14,739 --> 00:59:16,602
Opposites that fit perfectly.

748
00:59:16,834 --> 00:59:18,256
Oh really?

749
00:59:18,367 --> 00:59:20,998
- So you're fully on this ship now?
- Of course.

750
00:59:21,097 --> 00:59:22,257
He bribed me.

751
00:59:22,321 --> 00:59:24,226
Right? You bought me a game, didn't you?

752
00:59:24,400 --> 00:59:27,281
I knew there had to be benefits involved.

753
00:59:27,927 --> 00:59:29,192
You're so easy to buy.

754
00:59:31,290 --> 00:59:32,804
So Dao, what's next?

755
00:59:34,877 --> 00:59:36,155
What can I even do?

756
00:59:36,656 --> 00:59:37,714
If he's not okay with it,

757
00:59:37,946 --> 00:59:38,946
just tell me.

758
00:59:39,200 --> 00:59:40,694
- We'll go tell P'Fah.
- Whoa.

759
00:59:41,496 --> 00:59:43,188
I smell someone showing off his boyfriend.

760
00:59:44,377 --> 00:59:45,377
Ouch.

761
00:59:45,564 --> 00:59:46,564
That hurts.

762
00:59:47,330 --> 00:59:50,361
You guys think I won't do
anything, so you're getting bold.

763
00:59:50,811 --> 00:59:51,811
Damn it.

764
00:59:52,053 --> 00:59:53,749
If it were Nao, I'd rub my
foot on his face already.

765
00:59:53,773 --> 00:59:55,604
Whoa, someone's fired up.

766
00:59:56,428 --> 00:59:57,428
Hey!

767
00:59:57,739 --> 01:00:01,918
Stop it. You ate the whole ice cream yourself.
We're supposed to split it evenly, damn it.

768
01:00:16,502 --> 01:00:17,902
Waiting for your boyfriend's match?

769
01:00:18,665 --> 01:00:20,200
And who exactly forced me to come?

770
01:00:22,131 --> 01:00:23,659
So we can go back together.

771
01:00:23,968 --> 01:00:25,448
I saw that you didn't bring your car.

772
01:00:26,568 --> 01:00:28,237
Waiting for me a bit won't kill you.

773
01:00:31,177 --> 01:00:33,960
When I play football,
everyone stares at me.

774
01:00:34,964 --> 01:00:35,971
Good for you.

775
01:00:37,324 --> 01:00:38,669
Hey, don't be like that.

776
01:00:39,031 --> 01:00:40,031
You're supposed to say...

777
01:00:40,244 --> 01:00:42,528
"Someone's hitting on you? Then

778
01:00:43,988 --> 01:00:45,868
I'll have to come to
watch you play every day."

779
01:00:46,373 --> 01:00:47,773
Isn't that how it's supposed to go?

780
01:00:47,891 --> 01:00:48,891
No.

781
01:00:53,240 --> 01:00:54,687
Be jealous of me a little.

782
01:00:55,214 --> 01:00:56,586
Come on, be jealous.

783
01:00:57,432 --> 01:00:58,859
Please?

784
01:00:59,035 --> 01:01:00,035
Yeah?

785
01:01:01,285 --> 01:01:02,285
No.

786
01:01:07,552 --> 01:01:08,552
Hey, Mhor.

787
01:01:08,632 --> 01:01:09,632
Get over here.

788
01:01:11,555 --> 01:01:12,555
Well then,

789
01:01:14,277 --> 01:01:15,357
give me some encouragement.

790
01:01:27,602 --> 01:01:28,607
Do your best.

791
01:01:41,625 --> 01:01:42,808
Bring it on!

792
01:01:43,023 --> 01:01:46,771
Even if all of you attack
me at once, I can handle it.

793
01:01:56,717 --> 01:01:57,937
Hey, slide!

794
01:02:16,702 --> 01:02:17,702
What are you drawing?

795
01:02:18,909 --> 01:02:19,909
Finished already?

796
01:02:20,531 --> 01:02:21,531
Yeah.

797
01:02:21,888 --> 01:02:22,888
Did you watch just now?

798
01:02:23,648 --> 01:02:24,648
Mm.

799
01:02:29,048 --> 01:02:30,048
So? Was it fun?

800
01:02:33,205 --> 01:02:34,205
You played well.

801
01:02:36,562 --> 01:02:37,562
Me?

802
01:02:38,348 --> 01:02:39,348
Mm.

803
01:02:44,502 --> 01:02:45,822
When you compliment me like that,

804
01:02:47,663 --> 01:02:48,663
it makes me really happy.

805
01:03:37,228 --> 01:03:38,405
Why did you draw me?

806
01:03:42,220 --> 01:03:44,151
Because your smile is beautiful.

807
01:03:45,760 --> 01:03:47,208
I just wanted to keep it.

808
01:03:58,782 --> 01:03:59,804
You're unbelievable.

809
01:04:38,620 --> 01:04:41,223
Why are you doing this?
We're not even dating.

810
01:04:41,247 --> 01:04:44,256
I ask you to be my boyfriend
every hour. Just say yes already.

811
01:04:44,842 --> 01:04:45,922
Kim Taemin.

812
01:04:46,320 --> 01:04:46,885
Who's that?

813
01:04:47,154 --> 01:04:49,888
Oh, Daotok's client—the writer, right?

814
01:04:49,912 --> 01:04:52,977
I've got a feeling he's
not just an ordinary client.

815
01:04:53,060 --> 01:04:56,238
Are you free next month? I've
got an important race coming up.

816
01:04:56,512 --> 01:04:58,521
I was thinking of asking you to come watch.
